body:
Confirmed - this is related to an ambiguity in the positional argument in the CLI on an update.
Thanks for reporting this.

@mdeuser @dubeejw: we should add a test for this as part of the go CLI work.

@lzbj We don't have examples or docs yet explaining this type of feeds, but we are working on getting them available.
See #559 it contains some background and initial draft for the docs.
Examples of deamon that implements a feed are things like alarm and cloudant changes, which should be in openwhisk soon #336 #390

@rabbah i think this looks good. the only issue i can think of: should apiKey be required: true? 

i guess it isn't required at the package level, rather it is required at the action level. i.e. to invoke an action in this package requires an apiKey. but we suggest (bindTime:true) that it be provided ahead of time.

is this a start at the operational semantics of these annotations?

@lzbj I converted this issue to be for Dialog action, and created 3 more 587, 588, 589
Take into account that each one should have proper tests, and docs cover
I suggest to work on one first, this issue is already assigned to you, as you finish this one and is ready to pick the next one then assign at that time.
